{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7,"isBulletin":668},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Iscrizioni Centuripine","Libertini","1949","\u003Cspan>Guido Libertini, «Iscrizioni Centuripine», \u003Ci>Siculorum Gymnasium\u003C/i> 2 (1949): 91–97\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/VQURX85J",[8,293,389,452,508,555,616],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":30,"layoutDesc":32,"handNote":41,"date":204,"places":209,"geo":219,"country":214,"provenance":211,"provenanceGeo":223,"region":226,"settlement":227,"repository":228,"idno":232,"textLang":235,"tmNumber":239,"facsimile":240,"letterHeights":247,"publications":262,"zotero":268,"keywords":274,"html":285,"bibl":286,"bulletinDateSort":292,"citedRangeSort":287,"languageSort":236,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic002945","A gymnasiarch crowns a group of youths",{"_":12},"edited",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":23,"ana":24,"type":25,"subtype":26,"resp":28,"ref":29},"marble","#material.inorganic.stone","stone.unspecified",[27],"unspecified","#Coccato","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"ana":31},"#condition.fragment",{"layout":33},{"p":34,"rs":35,"damage":39},"15 neatly carved lines of Greek letters, of which the first four are larger. There appears to be a slight vacat at the top; lines 1-3 are indented by the equivalent of 1-2 characters at most; from line 4 onwards the left indentation increases, with clear vacats after lines 5 and 6, and a fixed left margin (c.7 cm vacat) from line 7 onwards; a vacat is consistently inserted between each name in the list from line 7 onwards.",{"_":36,"ana":37,"ref":38},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":40},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":42,"dimensions":170},[43,44],"Elegant letters with minimal serifs/terminations visible on longer strokes (e.g. on tau, sigma and epsilon). Alpha has straight bar; beta has smaller upper loop, with the two loops connected without meeting the vertical; epsilon has shorter middle bar; theta is a full-size circle with a detached horizontal stroke at the centre; kappa has full length arms; mu has near vertical first and last strokes, with the middle strokes meeting a small way above the baseline; xsi is formed of vertical with three horizontals, the middle one of shorter length; omicron is full-size; pi has equal length vertical strokes; sigma has horizontal topo and bottom strokes; phi is ovoid, with vertical taller than other letters (14-15mm); omega full size, near circular, but open at the base. Traces of a secondary text include lunate epsilon (see commentary).",{"_":45,"ref":46},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n             